1 Overview
**********

The `ggadt' program calculates the x-ray scattering properties of dust
in the interstellar medium. You define the geometry and composition of
a dust grain, the energy of the incident x-ray photons, and a few other
parameters.  The `ggadt' program then calculates the
orientationally-averaged scattering cross-section in the plane
perpendicular to the incident photons.

   GGADT was written by John Hoffman and Michael Tarczon.

